
A *RAID device* is a *virtual device* that is created from at least two → Linux/devices/index#block-devices[block devices].

table { rl
 ~Level~ ☰ ~Lost capacity~
  0 ☰ None
  1 ☰ 50 %
  5 ☰ 1 disk
  6 ☰ 2 disks
 10 ☰ 50 %
table }

? Linux supports software RAID devices through the *md* (multiple devices) device driver.

